This phenomenon seems to occur occasionally when rebooting the machine on which a bookie is running suddenly. I saw the same phenomenon occurred only once in our development environment.

The brokers in the development environment had been modified to output a thread dump using [ThreadDumpUtil](https://github.com/apache/pulsar/blob/v2.1.1-incubating/buildtools/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/tests/ThreadDumpUtil.java) just before shutdown.

```diff
diff --git a/pulsar-zookeeper-utils/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/zookeeper/ZooKeeperSessionWatcher.java b/pulsar-zookeeper-utils/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/zookeeper/ZooKeeperSessionWatcher.java
index d654a77..698fac9 100644
--- a/pulsar-zookeeper-utils/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/zookeeper/ZooKeeperSessionWatcher.java
+++ b/pulsar-zookeeper-utils/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/zookeeper/ZooKeeperSessionWatcher.java
@@ -156,6 +156,7 @@ public class ZooKeeperSessionWatcher implements Watcher, StatCallback, Runnable,
                         - TimeUnit.NANOSECONDS.toMillis(System.nanoTime() - disconnectedAt);
                 if (timeRemainingMillis <= 0) {
                     LOG.error("timeout expired for reconnecting, invoking shutdown service");
+                    LOG.info(ThreadDumpUtil.buildThreadDiagnosticString());
                     close();
                     shuttingDown = true;
                     shutdownService.shutdown(-1);
```

These are thread dumps just before the two brokers are shut down:

* [threaddump_broker1.txt](https://github.com/apache/pulsar/files/2855793/threaddump_broker1.txt)
* [threaddump_broker2.txt](https://github.com/apache/pulsar/files/2855794/threaddump_broker2.txt)

It seems to me that the problem is that `pulsar-ordered-OrderedExecutor-7-0-EventThread` and `pulsar-ordered-OrderedExecutor-3-0-EventThread` are waiting. These threads were watching events of ZK at each broker.

* [broker1.log](https://github.com/apache/pulsar/files/2855928/broker1.log)
* [broker2.log](https://github.com/apache/pulsar/files/2855929/broker2.log)

Does anyone know the cause of this problem?
